Task 1 Explain the working of following commands 

1) LOAD
it Loads data from the file system  into a relation.
a = load '/hadoopdata/pig/A.txt' using PigStorage(',') as (a1:int, a2:int, a3:int);

2) STORE
it saves a relation to the file system.
STORE l INTO '/pigoutput';

3) DUMP
it prints the contents of a relation on the console.
Dump a ;

4) FOREACH
it generates data transformations based on columns of data.
l = FOREACH c GENERATE a1, a2, a2*a3;

5) FILTER
it removes unwanted rows from a relation.
f = FILTER c by $1 > 3;

6) GROUP BY 
it groups the data in a single relation.
g = GROUP c by $2;
g = GROUP c by ($0,$1); 
h = GROUP c ALL;

7) ORDER BY 
it arranges a relation in a sorted order based on one or more fields (ascending or descending).
f = order c by a1 desc ;

8) DESCRIBE
it describes the schema of a relation.
describe f;
